=========================================================
PRINTF FORMAT SPECIFIERS â€” CHEATSHEET (RAW TEXT)
=========================================================

INTEGER TYPES
---------------------------------------------------------
Data Type                | Format | Example Output
-------------------------|--------|---------------
signed integer           | %d     | 42
signed integer           | %i     | 42
unsigned integer         | %u     | 42
short                    | %hd    | 42
unsigned short           | %hu    | 42
long                     | %ld    | 42
unsigned long            | %lu    | 42
long long                | %lld   | 42
unsigned long long       | %llu   | 42


FLOATING-POINT TYPES
---------------------------------------------------------
Data Type                | Format | Description
-------------------------|--------|-------------------------
float                    | %f     | decimal notation
double                   | %f     | decimal notation
long double              | %Lf    | decimal notation
scientific notation      | %e     | 1.23e+03
scientific notation      | %E     | 1.23E+03
compact format           | %g     | auto f / e
compact format           | %G     | auto f / E


CHARACTERS & STRINGS
---------------------------------------------------------
Data Type                | Format | Description
-------------------------|--------|-------------------------
character                | %c     | single character
string                   | %s     | null-terminated string
string (precision)       | %.Ns   | max N characters


POINTERS
---------------------------------------------------------
Data Type                | Format | Description
-------------------------|--------|-------------------------
pointer / address        | %p     | memory address


NUMBER BASES
---------------------------------------------------------
Base                     | Format | Example
-------------------------|--------|----------------
hexadecimal (lower)      | %x     | 2a
hexadecimal (upper)      | %X     | 2A
octal                    | %o     | 52
hex with prefix          | %#x    | 0x2a
octal with prefix        | %#o    | 052


WIDTH, PRECISION, ALIGNMENT
---------------------------------------------------------
Format                   | Meaning
-------------------------|--------------------------------
%5d                      | width 5, right-aligned
%-5d                     | width 5, left-aligned
%05d                     | width 5, zero-padded
%.2f                     | 2 digits after decimal
%8.2f                    | width 8, precision 2


BOOLEAN
---------------------------------------------------------
Data Type                | Format | Output
-------------------------|--------|---------
boolean                  | %d     | 0 or 1


MISCELLANEOUS
---------------------------------------------------------
Sequence                 | Meaning
-------------------------|----------------
%%                       | literal percent sign
\n                       | new line
\t                       | tab
\"                       | double quote
\\                       | backslash


IMPORTANT NOTES
---------------------------------------------------------
- Format specifier must match variable type
- Wrong specifier = undefined behavior
- %f is used for both float and double
- %lf is
